Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}(halved, peeled and sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @courgette{1}(trimmed) then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

== Fragrant Curry ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. Add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and cook until brown all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn occasionally.

> Tip: Do this in batches if necessary - you don't want to stew the chicken!

Add the shallot and cook, stirring, until soft, ~{5%minutes}.

== Limey Rice ==

Pour the @water{300%ml} into a saucepan and bring to the boil. When boiling, add @salt{1/4%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Simmering Curry ==

Add the garlic, half of the parsley and the @Zanzibar style curry powder{1} to the chicken. Cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the @coconut milk{200%ml} and @chicken stock powder{1}. Bring to the boil, stir and lower the heat so the curry simmers gently. Cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Add the courgette, then simmer until the sauce has thickened and the courgette is tender, ~{5-7%minutes}, add the @king prawns{150%g}(shelled and deveined) halfway though the courgette cook time to cook for ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the curry looks a bit dry.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the center.

== Assembly ==

While the curry is cooking, zest and halve the @lime{½}(zested and halved). When the rice is ready, fluff it up with a #fork{}. Stir in the lime zest and a small squeeze of lime juice (save some for the curry!).

When the curry is cooked, taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if required. Stir in the remaining parsley and a squeeze of lime juice. Spoon the rice into #bowls{}, top with the fragrant chicken curry and enjoy!